- Ensure full keyboard support for interactive components.
- Provide clear focus-visible styles for all focusable elements.
- Use semantic HTML before ARIA.
- Use ARIA roles and labels only when necessary.
- Provide accessible names for icons and buttons.
- Ensure screen-reader friendly content order.
- Verify WCAG AA contrast for all themes.
- Test interactive states with keyboard and screen readers.
- Avoid relying on color alone to convey information.